latestPosts.caption:
I am not a Filmmaker but just attempted to portray how vitiligo is treated in society —
Khoob-soorat is a short film that explores the journey of self-love and acceptance in a world that often struggles to see beyond the surface.
This one’s especially close to my heart because it’s about embracing the beauty that exists within.
Watch it on YouTube and let me know what resonates with you.

latestPosts.caption:
2 years back, I got a call and was asked to play Haseena in Gaanth chapter1 JamnaaPaar. You won't believe, but I denied in first go. Because I thought I cant act. Acting is something out of my league. But then a few days later, I got their call again asking to atleast give it a try and make the audition. And then I thought okay, lets try. And here it is. 2 years later, Haseena is here 💖

Presenting you some BTS. And ofcourse my excitement is clearly evident. 

Spot me in Gaanth chapter 1 Jamnaapaar only on Jio Cinema Premium and let me know how did you find it. 

Vitiligo, self love, self acceptance, vitiliglow, gaanth , gaanth chapter 1 Jamnapaar, gaanth on jio cinema 
vitiligo awareness, world vitiligo day 2024

#vitiligo #gaanthonjiocinema #gaanth #gaanthchapter1jamnaapaar

VITILIGO on Big Screen🥹💖
I have seen and heard about dreams coming true but trust me when I say this... This is purely a never seen dream coming true. I couldn't even dare to dream of something like this but I guess "ख़ुद ख़ुदा ने देखे थे ये ख़्वाब मेरे लिए" 
Extremely grateful to @lifeofvasu and @romilmodi22 for having found me out of nowhere. And to @kanishk.varma and @92sohambhattacharyya for selecting me for the character and also for bringing vitiligo into forefront. We need more people like you 💖 And a huge thanks to @aknain for helping me get through the audition. 
So guys, now Gaanth Chapter 1 Jamnpaar is all yours. Watch it on Jio Cinema Premium. And Spot me there. And after that, come to Anmol Spotted. This series getting released in the month of june, which is vitiligo awareness month is a sign of telling the world that the skin is just a costume. 

Signing off as Haseena, Anmol will see you guys at Anmol Spotted. 

16 june - Mumbai 
23 june - Delhi

Anmol Spotted – Where every spot has a story!✨

June is Vitiligo Awareness Month, and I am taking the stage again to share stories that matter. This isn’t just a show—it’s a celebration of courage, self-love, and the power of being seen.

Come join me in Delhi, Mumbai, and Jaipur as we spotlight the beauty of vitiligo—one heartfelt moment at a time.
